{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AWJguaJNAGTkGdU5eTzZ2L","type":"tool_result","content":"  1620→| Avg cost/story | $3.64 |\n  1621→| Estimated waste (no-op sessions) | ~$310+ (41%+) |\n  1622→| Top cost phase | verify (53.8%, $407.30) |\n  1623→| Top cost tool | Bash (35.0%, $264.63) |\n  1624→\n  1625→### Root Cause\n  1626→\n  1627→Ralph loads `sprint-state.json` once at startup, mutates in memory, and writes back each loop iteration. Its in-memory snapshot predates the completion of stories 16-5 through 16-8. Every loop iteration overwrites the on-disk state with the stale snapshot, reverting those 4 stories. The fix applied in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents phantom stories but does not prevent status reversion.\n  1628→\n  1629→### Action Required\n  1630→\n  1631→**Stop Ralph.** The sprint is complete. Every session since ~session 17 has been wasted on the same fix. 53 consecutive no-op sessions have burned an estimated $310+ in API costs for zero productive output.\n  1632→\n  1633→Fixes needed before restarting any autonomous loop:\n  1634→1. Sprint-complete exit condition (if all stories done, exit)\n  1635→2. Monotonic status guard (done -> anything-else = reject)\n  1636→3. Re-read state from disk before each write\n  1637→\n  1638→---\n  1639→\n  1640→*Session 69 retrospective generated 2026-03-28. Sprint is complete. Stop Ralph.*\n  1641→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01784CsBtHSnJ9qJkNqshvNs","session_id":"983184f3-104e-4213-8c13-c54137f128e0","uuid":"e1d6eef6-5e2c-4995-b8b0-b8cfc7b28255","timestamp":"2026-03-28T06:21:18.214Z"}
